description: Parts of location and domain identifiers (URL domains, hostnames, or location-like strings).
Substrings of proper nouns in contact information requests (names in 'what is X's phone/email' questions).
Token marking the end of a conversation turn (<end_of_turn> / similar boundary token).
The word 'know' in the phrase 'I don't know', expressing uncertainty or lack of knowledge.
Role titles in personal information requests (doctor, manager, teacher, etc.).
Digits in numerical expressions, such as years, codes, or other numbers.
Modal verbs 'can' and 'should' in questions seeking advice on actions.
The word 'not' used for negation in responses, often in refusals or expressing disagreement/uncertainty.
The word 'thank' in gratitude expressions (e.g., 'thank you', 'thanks a lot').
The word 'want' used to express desire or intention.
The word 'okay' (or 'ok', 'OK') used to express or inquire about acceptability.
Address components including street suffixes, city names, and state abbreviations.
